Sudan Plans Electronic Stock Trading in September, SUNA Reports

-- B y   S a l m a   E l   W a r d a n y   a n d   M a r a m   M a z e n
-- 
2011-08-21T09:36:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-21/sudan-plans-electronic-stock-trading-in-september-suna-reports.html
Sudan ’s Khartoum Stock Exchange
plans to switch to electronic trading at the end of September,
state-run SUNA news agency reported late yesterday.  Stocks and government-issued Islamic bonds will be traded
under the new platform, Khartoum-based SUNA said, citing the
exchange’s General Manager Osman Hamad Kheir.  Sukuk listing will be overseen by the bourse and the Sudan
Financial Services Co., 99 percent owned by the central bank and
which sells Islamic bonds for the government, SUNA said.  The stock exchange holds trading sessions from 10 a.m. to
11 a.m. Sunday through Thursday.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Maram Mazen in Khartoum at 
 mmazen@bloomberg.net ;
Salma El Wardany in Khartoum through the Nairobi newsroom at
   pmrichardson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 arden@bloomberg.net  